      "span_text": "This advantage is important when operating on a delicate tissue such as the anal canal mucosa because the atraumatic nature of the cut allows a dramatic reduction of tissue oedema with subsequent improvement of the postoperative pain (the chief concern of every proctologist). Radio surgery can simply be termed as an electro surgery at radiofrequency."
